HEADWORD: Daddle
<hw>Dad"dle</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧d"d'l)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Daddled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Daddling</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[Prob. freq. of <ets>dade</ets>.]</ety> <def>To toddle; to walk
unsteadily, like a child or an old man; hence, to do anything slowly or
feebly.</def>⟦br⟧
